Group Research Supervisor: Rongyong Zhao Apr.2019 May.2020
Designed a nutrition ordering system aiming to improve the college student's diet and efficiency of canteen dining. This

Perceptual Anthropomorphism of Autonomous Driving based on Spatio-Temporal Attention Guidance
Graduate Design Supervisor: Chen Chai March.2022 June.2022
The research aims to enhance the environmental awareness of autonomous vehicles via human-machine augmented
intelligence.
Extracted the eye movement data collected by YOLOV5 via a driving simulation experiment, research on drivers attention
mechanism and built the driver's attention training set. Based on 3D-CNN network, a two-branches neutral network model
is build to predict the significant zone of the dynamic traffic scene. Model consists of branch of traffic environment and
drivers consciousness branch. Compared with the traditional salient region detection model and spatial attention prediction
model, the two-branch spatio-temporal network model achieved more accurate prediction results of key environmental
regions in both simple and complex scenes.
Innovation and Entrepreneurship Training Project in Shanghai: Intersection Feature Parameter Recognition Based on
Floating Car Data
Group Research Supervisor: Wanjing Ma Apr.2020 May.2021
Simplified and analysed the GPS trajectory data of the Didi Taxi the city of Qingdao. Used the Delaunay triangulation
method to remove the noise points to filter the data. Used Gaussian Mixture Model, clustering and other intelligent
algorithms to achieve topological structure recognition, road centerline extraction, lane number recognition, turning point
extraction and intersection range recognition.
Responsible for designing technical approach. Also conducted the data processing algorithm, such as DBSCAN;
intersection recognition algorithm; clustering and lane count algorithm based on GMM, etc.
Realised the recognition accuracy of 89.31% of intersection recognition. The developed method of the research could reduce
2 / 3
the collection cost of intersection-channelised-information and shorten the information update cycle.
Magic Light Intelligent Traffic Signal Control Evaluation and Optimization System
Group Project Supervisor: Wanjing Ma Nov.2020 Jun.2021
Developed an urban traffic signal control evaluation and optimization system applicable at intersections with different
geometric conditions, various traffic conditions, and diversified control modes, aiming to optimize traffic jams and increase
traffic efficiency.
In charge of the data processing, extracting map information from the data, and embedding the algorithm in the platform.
This system won the First Prize of the 6th "Excellence Cup" of Tongji University.
PROJECT EXPERIENCE
Anti-epidemic Materials Transport and Emergency Plan based on Annealing and AHP
Competition Project May.2020
The models aimed to solved the anti-epidemic materials transport problem of Shanghai. Used normalization and
programming to build a multiple conditions Traveling Salesman Problem, and annealing to get the optimization strategy.
Built Logistic model to forecast number of infected people, and get emergency plan based on AHP considering medical
level and position factors.
In charge of building the three models, and programming in Python to get the solutions.
The models won the First Prize of Mathematical Modeling Contest of Tongji University.
A Physical Examination for the Higher Education System
Competition Project Feb.2021
Built a health diagnosis model for the higher education system, using factor analysis and entropy weight method to get
higher education system score based 12 indicators. And built a sustainability evaluation model, using gray forecast model
to predict factors and establishing sustainability evaluation indicators.
In charge of building the evaluation and prediction models, and programming.
The models won H Prize (equals Second Prize) of American College Student Mathematical Modeling Contest.
Warehouse Human Resource Management of Sinotrans Ltd.

This system won the First Prize of the Tongji University Internal Logistics Design Competition and Third Prize of the 7th
